<br>
If ya hit ya'll likely get over 21 (remember 10 is roughly a 30% chance, 6-9 is another 30% - not countin what's out so far). Basically a coin toss  (ok 40%win vs 60%lose is a weighted coin). Then the bank gets to draw (with that 30% chance of gettin a 19, which still beats half of the 17-21 numbers).<br>
<br>
If ya stand, that's a 52% chance ya lose directly (bank draws 8-11), and the bank can even get over 16 with the other draws (not about to calculate those odds). Standin kills ya here.<br>
<br>
If ya split ya basically stand slightly inferior odds than the bank, twice. Seems to be the reasonable choice here imho. <br>
<br>
